Scott Boehm/AP The Week 14 game between the Bears and Packers Sunday, Dec. 7 at Lambeau Field in Green Bay has been flexed from noon to 3:25 p.m. CT, the NFL announced Thursday. It's the first of two matchups this season between the longtime rivals, both of whom are in playoff contention. The Bears (7-3) enter Week 12 in first place in the NFC North, ahead of the Packers (6-3-1), Lions (6-4) and Vikings (4-6). The second meeting between the Bears and Packers this year will be held at Soldier Field Saturday, Dec. 20 at a time that has yet to be determined. Related Content news Bears players posting strong showing in Pro Bowl fan voting 15 Bears players are in the top 10 in Pro Bowl voting at their respective positions. Pro Bowl voting runs through Dec. 15. Fans can vote for their favorite Bears by visiting ChicagoBears.com/ProBowl. news Chicago Bears announce ticketing information for potential home postseason games The Chicago Bears on Tuesday announced that the club will begin selling tickets for potential home games for the 2025 Postseason. Single-game tickets for a potential NFC Wild Card home game and a potential NFC Divisional Round home game will go on sale to the public at 11:00 a.m. CT on Thursday, December 11, at ChicagoBears.com/Tickets. news 5 things that stood out to Bears coach Ben Johnson in Week 14 loss After watching tape of Sunday's 28-21 loss to the Packers, Bears coach Ben Johnson spoke to reporters Monday about what was responsible for the offense's second-half resurgence, why the Bears drained the clock late in regulation and more. news By the Numbers: Bears at Packers | 2025 Week 14 Senior writer Larry Mayer discusses some notable numbers and stats from the Bears' 28-21 loss to the Packers Sunday at Lambeau Field.
